cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about a deep learning architecture for single image dehazing, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel Feature Attention module, which involves learning feature weights, and a Feature Fusion structure, which combines features from different levels. These aspects suggest that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper includes experimental results that involve image quality metrics, which could make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
